<doc id="1129119" wikidata="Q1050044" url="?curid=1129119" title="CatCat">
<text>CatCat is a Finnish duo that participated in the Eurovision Song Contest in 1994 with the song &quot;Bye Bye Baby&quot;. They reached 22nd place with 11 points. Members of the duo are sisters Katja and Virpi whose original surname &quot;Kätkä&quot; is &quot;Kätkät&quot; in plural form which sounds exactly like CatCat, hence the name.

== Albums ==

* CatCat (1992)
* Bye Bye Baby (1994)
* Viides kevät (1994)
* Enkeli (Angel) (1995)
* Yö ja päivä (Night and day) (2001)
* Parhaat (2002) (collection)
* Hitit (2004) (collection)

