<text>The men&#x27;s Greco-Roman 55 kilograms at the [[2004 Summer Olympics]] as part of the wrestling program were held at the Ano Liosia Olympic Hall, August 24 to August 25. The competition held with an elimination system of three or four wrestlers in each pool, with the winners qualify for the quarterfinals, semifinals and final by way of direct elimination.

