<text>The 125th General Assembly comprised the state legislature of the U.S. state of Ohio. The senate is the upper house of the Ohio General Assembly. Every two years, half of the senate seats come up for election. The 125th General Assembly was in session in 2003 and 2004. The party distribution was 22 Republicans and 11 Democrats.

